als#Health_and_fitness" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Health</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#History_and_events" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">History</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Mathematics_and_logic" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Mathematics</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Natural_and_physical_sciences" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Nature</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#People_and_self" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">People</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Philosophy_and_thinking" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Philosophy</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Religion_and_belief_systems" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Religion</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Society_and_social_sciences" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Society</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Technology_and_applied_sciences" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Technology</a></dd>\n</dl>\n</div>\n<p><br /></p>\n<div style="background:#FFFFFF; padding:20px;">\n<div style="clear:both; width:100%;">\n<div style="text-align:center; padding-bottom:.9em;"><span style="font-size:200%; font-family:Segoe UI; color:#373737;">The&#160;&#160;</span><a href="/wiki/File:Microsoft_logo_(2012).svg" class="image"><img alt="Microsoft logo" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/Microsoft_logo_%282012%29.svg/200px-Microsoft_logo_%282012%29.svg.png" width="200" height="43" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/Microsoft_logo_%282012%29.svg/300px-Microsoft_logo_%282012%29.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/Microsoft_logo_%282012%29.svg/400px-Microsoft_logo_%282012%29.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="512" data-file-height="109" /></a><span style="font-size:200%; color:#373737; font-family:Segoe UI;">&#160;&#160;Portal</span></div>\n<div style="clear: both;"></div>\n<div style="position: relative;border: 0px solid #ababab;background: #f25022;color: #FFFFFF;padding: 7.5px;text-align: center;font-weight: bold;font-size: 15px;margin-bottom: 0px;border-top: 0px solid #ababab&#160;;border-bottom: none;"><span class="plainlinks" style="position: absolute;top: 1px;right: 40px;background: transparent;border: 0px;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%;font-weight: normal;color: #FFFFFF;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft/Intro&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #FFFFFF">edit</span></a> &#160;</span><span class="plainlinks" style="position: absolute;top: 1px;right: 1px;background: transparent;border: 0px;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%;font-weight: normal;color: #FFFFFF;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft/Intro&amp;action=watch"><span style="color: #FFFFFF">watch</span></a> &#160;</span>\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#FFFFFF"><span class="mw-headline" id=".C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0The_Microsoft_Portal"></span></h2>\n<div style="text-align:left;">\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#FFFFFF">&#160;&#160;<span style="font-family:Segoe UI Semibold, Segoe;">&#160;&#160;&#160;The Microsoft Portal</span></h2>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="display: block;border: 0px solid #ababab;border-bottom: 0px solid #ababab;vertical-align: top;background: #FFFFFF;color: #373737;margin-bottom: 10px;padding: 1em;margin-top: 0em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div style="position:relative;top:-3em"><span id="P:MS"></span></div>\n<div class="shortcutbox plainlist noprint" role="note" style="float:right;border:1px solid #aaa;background:#fff;margin:.3em .3em .3em 1em;padding:.4em .6em;text-align:center;font-size:smaller;line-height:2em;font-weight:bold"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Shortcut" title="Wikipedia:Shortcut">Shortcut</a>:\n<ul>\n<li><span class="plainlinks"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=P:MS&amp;redirect=no">P:MS</a></span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div style="float:left;margin-right:1.5em">\n<p><a href="/wiki/File:Microsoft_CES_2009.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Microsoft CES 2009.jpg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/Microsoft_CES_2009.jpg/270px-Microsoft_CES_2009.jpg" width="270" height="180" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/Microsoft_CES_2009.jpg/405px-Microsoft_CES_2009.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/Microsoft_CES_2009.jpg/540px-Microsoft_CES_2009.jpg 2x" data-file-width="3456" data-file-height="2304" /></a></p>\n</div>\n<p><b>Microsoft</b> (<a href="/wiki/NASDAQ" title="NASDAQ">NASDAQ</a>:&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.nasdaq.com/symbol/msft">MSFT</a>) is an American <a href="/wiki/Public_company" title="Public company">public</a> <a href="/wiki/Multinational_corporation" title="Multinational corporation">multinational corporation</a> headquartered in <a href="/wiki/Redmond,_Washington" title="Redmond, Washington">Redmond, Washington</a>, USA that develops, manufactures, licenses, and supports a wide range of products and services predominantly related to <a href="/wiki/Computing" title="Computing">computing</a> through its various product divisions.</p>\n<p>Its most profitable products are <a href="/wiki/Microsoft_Office" title="Microsoft Office">Microsoft Office</a>, which has come to dominate the <a href="/wiki/Commercial_software" title="Commercial software">commercial</a> <a href="/wiki/Office_suite" class="mw-redirect" title="Office suite">office suite</a> market, and the <a href="/wiki/Microsoft_Windows" title="Microsoft Windows">Microsoft Windows</a> <a href="/wiki/Operating_system" title="Operating system">operating system</a>, which has achieved near ubiquity in the <a href="/wiki/Desktop_computer" title="Desktop computer">desktop computer</a> market. The company has also diversified in recent years into the video game industry with the <a href="/wiki/Xbox" title="Xbox">Xbox</a>, its successor, the <a href="/wiki/Xbox_360" title="Xbox 360">Xbox 360</a> and most recently the <a href="/wiki/Xbox_One" title="Xbox One">Xbox One</a> as well as into the <a href="/wiki/Consumer_electronics" title="Consumer electronics">consumer electronics</a> and digital services market with <a href="/wiki/Bing_(search_engine)" title="Bing (search engine)">Bing</a>, <a href="/wiki/MSN" title="MSN">MSN</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Windows_Phone" title="Windows Phone">Windows Phone</a> OS.</p>\n<p><br /></p>\n<div align="right"><b><a href="/wiki/Microsoft" title="Microsoft">More about Microsoft...</a></b></div>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="text-align:center; margin:0.25em auto 0.75em"><span class="noprint plainlinks purgelink"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft&amp;action=purge"><span title="Purge this page"><b>View new selections below</b> (purge)</span></a></span></div>\n<div class="portal-column-left">\n<div style="clear: both;"></div>\n<div style="position: relative;border: 0px solid #ababab;background: #00a4ef;color: #FFFFFF;padding: 7.5px;text-align: center;font-weight: bold;font-size: 15px;margin-bottom: 0px;border-top: 0px solid #ababab&#160;;border-bottom: none;"><span class="plainlinks" style="position: absolute;top: 1px;right: 40px;background: transparent;border: 0px;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%;font-weight: normal;color: #FFFFFF;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft/Selected_article/10&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #FFFFFF">edit</span></a> &#160;</span><span class="plainlinks" style="position: absolute;top: 1px;right: 1px;background: transparent;border: 0px;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%;font-weight: normal;color: #FFFFFF;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft/Selected_article/10&amp;action=watch"><span style="color: #FFFFFF">watch</span></a> &#160;</span>\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#FFFFFF"><span class="mw-headline" id=".C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0Selected_article"></span></h2>\n<div style="text-align:left;">\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#FFFFFF">&#160;&#160;<span style="font-family:Segoe UI Semibold, Segoe;">&#160;&#160;&#160;Selected article</span></h2>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="display: block;border: 0px solid #ababab;border-bottom: 0px solid #ababab;vertical-align: top;background: #FFFFFF;color: #373737;margin-bottom: 10px;padding: 1em;margin-top: 0em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Windows_2000" title="Windows 2000">Windows 2000</a></b> is a business-oriented graphical <a href="/wiki/Operating_system" title="Operating system">operating system</a> that was designed to work with either <a href="/wiki/Uniprocessor" class="mw-redirect" title="Uniprocessor">uniprocessor</a> or <a href="/wiki/Symmetric_multiprocessing" title="Symmetric multiprocessing">symmetric multi-processor</a> (SMP) <a href="/wiki/32-bit" title="32-bit">32-bit</a> <a href="/wiki/Intel" title="Intel">Intel</a> <a href="/wiki/X86" title="X86">x86</a> computers. It is part of the <a href="/wiki/Microsoft" title="Microsoft">Microsoft</a> <a href="/wiki/Windows_NT" title="Windows NT">Windows NT</a> line of operating systems and was released on <a href="/wiki/February_17" title="February 17">February 17</a> <a href="/wiki/2000" title="2000">2000</a>, but has since been superseded by newer Microsoft operating systems. Windows 2000 came in four versions: Professional, Server, Advanced Server, and Datacenter Server. Additionally, Microsoft offered Windows 2000 Advanced Server Limited Edition, which was released in 2001 and runs on <a href="/wiki/64-bit" class="mw-redirect" title="64-bit">64-bit</a> Intel <a href="/wiki/Itanium" title="Itanium">Itanium</a> <a href="/wiki/Microprocessor" title="Microprocessor">microprocessors</a>. Windows 2000 is <a href="/wiki/Preemption_(computing)" title="Preemption (computing)">preemptible</a> and interruptible, and is classified as a <a href="/wiki/Hybrid_kernel" title="Hybrid kernel">hybrid kernel</a> <a href="/wiki/Operating_system" title="Operating system">operating system</a>, as its <a href="/wiki/Architecture_of_the_Windows_NT_operating_system_line" class="mw-redirect" title="Architecture of the Windows NT operating system line">architecture</a> is divided into <a href="/wiki/User_mode" class="mw-redirect" title="User mode">user mode</a> and <a href="/wiki/Kernel_mode" class="mw-redirect" title="Kernel mode">kernel mode</a>. The kernel mode provides unrestricted access to system resources and facilitates the user mode, which is heavily restricted and designed for most applications. All versions of Windows 2000 have common functionality, including many system utilities such as the <a href="/wiki/Microsoft_Management_Console" title="Microsoft Management Console">Microsoft Management Console</a> and standard system management applications such as a disk defragmentation utility.</p>\n<table class="noprint" width="100%" border="0" style="padding: 0; margin: 0; background-color:transparent">\n<tr>\n<td width="33%">\n<div style="text-align:left;"><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Microsoft/Selected_article" title="Portal:Microsoft/Selected article">...Archive/Nominations</a></b></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div style="text-align:right;margin-right:10px;margin-bottom:4px;">\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Windows_2000" title="Windows 2000">More...</a></b></p>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both;"></div>\n<div style="position: relative;border: 0px solid #ababab;background: #00a4ef;color: #FFFFFF;padding: 7.5px;text-align: center;font-weight: bold;font-size: 15px;margin-bottom: 0px;border-top: 0px solid #ababab&#160;;border-bottom: none;"><span class="plainlinks" style="position: absolute;top: 1px;right: 40px;background: transparent;border: 0px;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%;font-weight: normal;color: #FFFFFF;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft/Selected_picture/4&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #FFFFFF">edit</span></a> &#160;</span><span class="plainlinks" style="position: absolute;top: 1px;right: 1px;background: transparent;border: 0px;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%;font-weight: normal;color: #FFFFFF;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft/Selected_picture/4&amp;action=watch"><span style="color: #FFFFFF">watch</span></a> &#160;</span>\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#FFFFFF"><span class="mw-headline" id=".C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0Selected_picture"></span></h2>\n<div style="text-align:left;">\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#FFFFFF">&#160;&#160;<span style="font-family:Segoe UI Semibold, Segoe;">&#160;&#160;&#160;Selected picture</span></h2>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="display: block;border: 0px solid #ababab;border-bottom: 0px solid #ababab;vertical-align: top;background: #FFFFFF;color: #373737;margin-bottom: 10px;padding: 1em;margin-top: 0em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div class="center">\n<div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Xbox_and_controller.jpeg" class="image" title="Xbox console"><img alt="Xbox console" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Xbox_and_controller.jpeg/300px-Xbox_and_controller.jpeg" width="300" height="225" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Xbox_and_controller.jpeg/450px-Xbox_and_controller.jpeg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Xbox_and_controller.jpeg/600px-Xbox_and_controller.jpeg 2x" data-file-width="800" data-file-height="600" /></a></div>\n</div>\n<table class="noprint" width="100%" border="0" style="padding: 0; margin: 0; background-color:transparent">\n<tr>\n<td width="33%">\n<center><small>Credit: <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:TimothyPilgrim" class="extiw" title="commons:User:TimothyPilgrim">Timothy Pilgrim</a></small></center>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>The <b><a href="/wiki/Xbox" title="Xbox">Xbox</a></b> is a <a href="/wiki/Video_game_console" title="Video game console">video game console</a> manufactured by <a href="/wiki/Microsoft" title="Microsoft">Microsoft</a>. It was released on November 15, 2001 in North America, February 22, 2002 in Japan, and March 14, 2002 in Australia and Europe. It was Microsoft\'s first foray into the gaming console market.</p>\n<table class="noprint" width="100%" border="0" style="padding: 0; margin: 0; background-color:transparent">\n<tr>\n<td width="33%">\n<div style="text-align:left;"><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Microsoft/Selected_picture" title="Portal:Microsoft/Selected picture">...Archive/Nominations</a></b></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div style="text-align:right;margin-right:10px;margin-bottom:4px;">\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Xbox" title="Xbox">More...</a></b></p>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both;"></div>\n<div style="position: relative;border: 0px solid #ababab;background: #f25022;color: #FFFFFF;padding: 7.5px;text-align: center;font-weight: bold;font-size: 15px;margin-bottom: 0px;border-top: 0px solid #ababab&#160;;border-bottom: none;"><span class="plainlinks" style="position: absolute;top: 1px;right: 40px;background: transparent;border: 0px;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%;font-weight: normal;color: #FFFFFF;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft/News&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #FFFFFF">edit</span></a> &#160;</span><span class="plainlinks" style="position: absolute;top: 1px;right: 1px;background: transparent;border: 0px;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%;font-weight: normal;color: #FFFFFF;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft/News&amp;action=watch"><span style="color: #FFFFFF">watch</span></a> &#160;</span>\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#FFFFFF"><span class="mw-headline" id=".C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0In_the_news"></span></h2>\n<div style="text-align:left;">\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#FFFFFF">&#160;&#160;<span style="font-family:Segoe UI Semibold, Segoe;">&#160;&#160;&#160;In the news</span></h2>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="display: block;border: 0px solid #ababab;border-bottom: 0px solid #ababab;vertical-align: top;background: #FFFFFF;color: #373737;margin-bottom: 10px;padding: 1em;margin-top: 0em;padding-top: .3em;"><b><a href="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki/Portal:Microsoft" class="extiw" title="wikinews:Portal:Microsoft">Wikinews Microsoft portal</a></b>\n<div style="float:right;margin-left:0.9em"><a href="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki/Main_Page" title="Read and edit Wikinews"><img alt="Read and edit Wikinews" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Wikinews-logo.svg/75px-Wikinews-logo.svg.png" width="75" height="41" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Wikinews-logo.svg/113px-Wikinews-logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Wikinews-logo.svg/150px-Wikinews-logo.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="759" data-file-height="415" /></a></div>\n<p><b>2016</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/June_13" title="June 13">June 13</a>: Microsoft announced an acquisition of <a href="/wiki/LinkedIn" title="LinkedIn">LinkedIn</a> for <span style="white-space: nowrap">US$</span>26.2B<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">[1]</a></sup></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/October_26" title="October 26">October 26</a>: Microsoft announces the <a href="/wiki/Surface_Studio" title="Surface Studio">Surface Studio</a> and <a href="/wiki/Surface_Dial" class="mw-redirect" title="Surface Dial">Surface Dial</a><sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/November_2" title="November 2">November 2</a>: <a href="/wiki/Microsoft_Teams" title="Microsoft Teams">Microsoft Teams</a>, a cloud-based team collaboration tool, is launched as part of <a href="/wiki/Office_365" title="Office 365">Office 365</a><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup></li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>2017</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/January_13" title="January 13">January 13</a>: Microsoft acquired Canadian artificial intelligence company, <a href="/wiki/Maluuba" title="Maluuba">Maluuba</a><sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/May_1" title="May 1">May 1</a>: Microsoft announces the first generation <a href="/wiki/Surface_Laptop" title="Surface Laptop">Surface Laptop</a> and <a href="/wiki/Windows_10_S" class="mw-redirect" title="Windows 10 S">Windows 10 S</a>, an operating system designed for schools which only supports software from the <a href="/wiki/Windows_Store" title="Windows Store">Windows Store</a><sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/May_10" title="May 10">May 10</a>: At Build 2017, <a href="/wiki/Visual_Studio" class="mw-redirect" title="Visual Studio">Visual Studio</a> is launched for <a href="/wiki/MacOS" title="MacOS">macOS</a> users<sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/May_23" title="May 23">May 23</a>: The <a href="/wiki/Surface_Pro_(5th_generation)" class="mw-redirect" title="Surface Pro (5th generation)">fifth-generation Surface Pro</a> is unveiled in <a href="/wiki/Shanghai" title="Shanghai">Shanghai</a><sup id="cite_ref-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/June_1" title="June 1">June 1</a>: The <a href="/wiki/Skype" title="Skype">Skype</a> applications are redesigned, in an attempt to appeal to a younger audience<sup id="cite_ref-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/June_12" title="June 12">June 12</a>: Microsoft unveils the <a href="/wiki/Xbox_One_X" class="mw-redirect" title="Xbox One X">Xbox One X</a> (also known as Project Scorpio) at <a href="/wiki/Electronic_Entertainment_Expo_2017" title="Electronic Entertainment Expo 2017">E3 2017</a><sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-9">[9]</a></sup></li>\n</ul>\n<p><br /></p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="portal-column-right">\n<div style="clear: both;"></div>\n<div style="position: relative;border: 0px solid #ababab;background: #00a4ef;color: #FFFFFF;padding: 7.5px;text-align: center;font-weight: bold;font-size: 15px;margin-bottom: 0px;border-top: 0px solid #ababab&#160;;border-bottom: none;"><span class="plainlinks" style="position: absolute;top: 1px;right: 40px;background: transparent;border: 0px;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%;font-weight: normal;color: #FFFFFF;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft/Selected_biography/1&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #FFFFFF">edit</span></a> &#160;</span><span class="plainlinks" style="position: absolute;top: 1px;right: 1px;background: transparent;border: 0px;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%;font-weight: normal;color: #FFFFFF;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft/Selected_biography/1&amp;action=watch"><span style="color: #FFFFFF">watch</span></a> &#160;</span>\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#FFFFFF"><span class="mw-headline" id=".C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0Selected_biography"></span></h2>\n<div style="text-align:left;">\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#FFFFFF">&#160;&#160;<span style="font-family:Segoe UI Semibold, Segoe;">&#160;&#160;&#160;Selected biography</span></h2>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="display: block;border: 0px solid #ababab;border-bottom: 0px solid #ababab;vertical-align: top;background: #FFFFFF;color: #373737;margin-bottom: 10px;padding: 1em;margin-top: 0em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div style="float:right;margin-left:0.2em"><a href="/wiki/File:Bill_Gates_2004_cr.jpg" class="image" title="Bill Gates"><img alt="Bill Gates" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Bill_Gates_2004_cr.jpg/100px-Bill_Gates_2004_cr.jpg" width="100" height="120" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Bill_Gates_2004_cr.jpg/150px-Bill_Gates_2004_cr.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Bill_Gates_2004_cr.jpg/200px-Bill_Gates_2004_cr.jpg 2x" data-file-width="428" data-file-height="513" /></a></div>\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Bill_Gates" title="Bill Gates">Bill Gates</a></b> (correctly William Henry Gates III) (born October 28, 1955 in <a href="/wiki/Seattle" title="Seattle">Seattle</a>) is the co-founder, <a href="/wiki/Chairman" title="Chairman">chairman</a>, former <a href="/wiki/Software_architecture" title="Software architecture">chief software architect</a>, and former <a href="/wiki/Chief_executive_officer" title="Chief executive officer">CEO</a> of <a href="/wiki/Microsoft" title="Microsoft">Microsoft</a>, the world\'s largest software company. According to <i><a href="/wiki/Forbes" title="Forbes">Forbes</a></i> magazine\'s list of <a href="/wiki/The_World%27s_Billionaires" title="The World\'s Billionaires">The World\'s Billionaires</a>, he was ranked as the richest person in the world for thirteen consecutive years, and recent estimates put his net worth near $82 billion dollars. When family wealth is considered, his family ranks second behind the <a href="/wiki/Walton_family" title="Walton family">Walton family</a>. Gates is one of the best-known entrepreneurs of the <a href="/wiki/Personal_computer" title="Personal computer">personal computer</a> revolution. Although he is widely respected by people who see his wealth as a product of intelligence and foresight, since amassing his fortune, Gates has pursued a number of <a href="/wiki/Philanthropy" title="Philanthropy">philanthropic</a> endeavors, donating large amounts of money to various charitable organizations and scientific research programs through the <a href="/wiki/Bill_%26_Melinda_Gates_Foundation" title="Bill &amp; Melinda Gates Foundation">Bill &amp; Melinda Gates Foundation</a>, established in 2000.</p>\n<table class="noprint" width="100%" border="0" style="padding: 0; margin: 0; background-color:transparent">\n<tr>\n<td width="33%">\n<div style="text-align:left;"><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Microsoft/Selected_biography" title="Portal:Microsoft/Selected biography">...Archive/Nominations</a></b></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div style="text-align:right;margin-right:10px;margin-bottom:4px;">\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Bill_Gates" title="Bill Gates">More...</a></b></p>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both;"></div>\n<div style="position: relative;border: 0px solid #ababab;background: #7fba00;color: #FFFFFF;padding: 7.5px;text-align: center;font-weight: bold;font-size: 15px;margin-bottom: 0px;border-top: 0px solid #ababab&#160;;border-bottom: none;"><span class="plainlinks" style="position: absolute;top: 1px;right: 40px;background: transparent;border: 0px;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%;font-weight: normal;color: #FFFFFF;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft/Did_you_know&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #FFFFFF">edit</span></a> &#160;</span><span class="plainlinks" style="position: absolute;top: 1px;right: 1px;background: transparent;border: 0px;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%;font-weight: normal;color: #FFFFFF;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft/Did_you_know&amp;action=watch"><span style="color: #FFFFFF">watch</span></a> &#160;</span>\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#FFFFFF"><span class="mw-headline" id=".C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0Did_you_know..."></span></h2>\n<div style="text-align:left;">\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#FFFFFF">&#160;&#160;<span style="font-family:Segoe UI Semibold, Segoe;">&#160;&#160;&#160;Did you know...</span></h2>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="display: block;border: 0px solid #ababab;border-bottom: 0px solid #ababab;vertical-align: top;background: #FFFFFF;color: #373737;margin-bottom: 10px;padding: 1em;margin-top: 0em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<ul>\n<li>... that <a href="/wiki/Windows_XP" title="Windows XP">Windows XP</a>\'s default <a href="/wiki/Bliss_(image)" title="Bliss (image)">Bliss</a> wallpaper was taken north of San Francisco in 1996?</li>\n<li>... that Microsoft\'s revenues on <a href="/wiki/Microsoft_Office" title="Microsoft Office">Microsoft Office</a> are in the range of $250 million USD a week?</li>\n<li>... that <a href="/wiki/Turing_Award" title="Turing Award">Turing Award</a> winner and long-time <a href="/wiki/Microsoft_Research" title="Microsoft Research">Microsoft Research</a> technical fellow <a href="/wiki/James_N._Gray" class="mw-redirect" title="James N. Gray">Jim Gray</a> was lost at sea during a solo sailing trip?</li>\n<li>... that <a href="/wiki/Robert_Fripp" title="Robert Fripp">Robert Fripp</a>, founding member of <a href="/wiki/King_Crimson" title="King Crimson">King Crimson</a>, helped create the system sounds for <a href="/wiki/Windows_Vista" title="Windows Vista">Windows Vista</a>?</li>\n<li>... that brand consultancy Millward Brown Optimor reported in 2006 that "Microsoft" is the most powerful brand name in the world?</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br /></p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both;"></div>\n<div style="position: relative;border: 0px solid #ababab;background: #ffb900;color: #FFFFFF;padding: 7.5px;text-align: center;font-weight: bold;font-size: 15px;margin-bottom: 0px;border-top: 0px solid #ababab&#160;;border-bottom: none;"><span class="plainlinks" style="position: absolute;top: 1px;right: 40px;background: transparent;border: 0px;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%;font-weight: normal;color: #FFFFFF;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft/Categories&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #FFFFFF">edit</span></a> &#160;</span><span class="plainlinks" style="position: absolute;top: 1px;right: 1px;background: transparent;border: 0px;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%;font-weight: normal;color: #FFFFFF;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Microsoft/Categories&amp;action=watch"><span style="color: #FFFFFF">watch</span></a> &#160;</span>\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#FFFFFF"><span class="mw-headline" id=".C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0.C2.A0Categories"></span></h2>\n<div style="text-align:left;">\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#FFFFFF">&#160;&#160;<span style="font-family:Segoe UI Semibold, Segoe;">&#160;&#160;&#160;Categories</span></h2>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="display: block;border: 0px solid #ababab;border-bottom: 0px solid #ababab;vertical-align: top;background: #FFFFFF;color: #373737;margin-bottom: 10px;padding: 1em;margin-top: 0em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div class="floatright"><a href="/wiki/File:M_box.svg" class="image" title="Microsoft categories"><img alt="Microsoft categories" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/M_box.svg/50px-M_box.svg.png" width="50" height="50" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/M_box.svg/75px-M_box.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/M_box.svg/100px-M_box.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="220" data-file-height="220" /></a></div>\n<div class="div-col columns column-count column-count-2" style="-moz-column-count: 2; -webkit-column-count: 2; column-count: 2;">\n<div style="font-size:85%;">\n<div class="CategoryTreeTag" data-ct-mode="0" data-ct-options="{&quot;mode&quot;:0,&quot;hideprefix&quot;:20,&quot;showcount&quot;:false,&quot;namespaces&quot;:false}">\n<div class="CategoryTreeSection">\n<div class="CategoryTreeItem"><span class="CategoryTreeBullet"><span class="CategoryTreeToggle" style="display: none;" data-ct-title="Microsoft" title="collapse" data-ct-loaded="1" data-ct-state="expanded">\xe2\x96\xbc</span></span> <a class="CategoryTreeLabel  CategoryTreeLabelNs14 CategoryTreeLabelCategory" href="/wiki/Category:Microsoft">Microsoft</a></div>\n<div class="CategoryTreeChildren" style="display:block">\n<div class="CategoryTreeSection">\n<div class="CategoryTreeItem"><span class="CategoryTreeBullet"><span class="CategoryTreeToggle" style="display: none;" data-ct-title="Microsoft_acquisitions" title="expand" data-ct-state="collapsed">\xe2\x96\xba</span></span> <a class="CategoryTreeLabel  CategoryTreeLabelNs14 CategoryTreeLabelCategory" href="/wiki/Category:Microsoft_acquisitions">Microsoft acquisitions</a></div>\n<div class="CategoryTreeChildren" style="display:none"></div>\n</div>\n<di